Scores of people from all over KZN together with the MEC of Health Dr Sibongiseni Dhlomo and executive members of the council gathered this morning, Friday 14 July, in King Dinizulu Park for a peaceful march against gender based abuse against women and children.The march started at 10:30 and proceeded through Pixley ka Seme, Samora Machel and finished at Gugu Dlaini Park where the MEC of Health addressed the public against gender based violence against women ad children, near the Workshop Shopping Mall.&#8220;Real men must stand up and defend the most vulnerable members of society women and children. We must not stand by and watch this terrible scourge tear apart the fabric of our communities and society. said KwaZulu-Natal Premier Willies Mchunu